Build CMake Docker SDK Toolchain Project 
execute the test only when test_docker_build parameter are set. Set test_docker_build to blank to skip this test case.
a) in project explorer, create new c/c++ project with Cmake hello world template and Yocto Project SDK CMake Toolchain (alpha) toolchain
b) right click on the project, go to configure and select  "Configure/Configure as Yocto Project CMake project (alpha)" 
c) in prompted project properties select SDK toolchain profile -> click "apply and close"
d) in project explorer, right click select properties
e) in properties windows, expand C/C++ build -> select Setting  
g) select container setting tab, check "build inside Docker Image" -> select an Image -> click "Apply" .
h) select "Yocto Project (alpha)" at left panel -> select Docker SDK toolchain profile -> click "Apply " -> click "Apply and Close".
i) refresh project explorer tab  
j) pin "CDT Global Build Consolse"
k) right click on project -> select "Regenerate CMake build files" -> validate docker image and toolchain in console .
l) right click on project -> select "Build Project"-> validate docker image and toolchain in console.
